javaslang

Class Functions

  • java.lang.Object
    • javaslang.Functions

  • public final class Functions
extends Object

    The class of reflective checked and unchecked functions with a specific return types.

    The type 位 'lambda' is the mother of all functions.

    There are checked functions Functions.CheckedFunction0 to Functions.CheckedFunction13, short: Functions.X0 to Functions.X13 (Note: X stands for 'eXception'. The lambda symbol 位 is hidden in X, just leave out the upper right line). Checked functions throw Throwable.
    And there are unchecked functions Functions.Function0 to Functions.Function13, short: Functions.位0 to Functions.位13. Unchecked functions are special checked functions, they throw a RuntimeException instead of Throwable.

    Additionally to that there are checked versions of all functions located in the Java package java.util.function.

    This class is not intended to be extended.

      • getLambdaSignature

        public static java.lang.invoke.MethodType getLambdaSignature(Serializable lambda)

        Gets the runtime method signature of the given lambda instance. Especially this function is handy when the functional interface is generic and the parameter and/or return types cannot be determined directly.

        Uses internally the SerializedLambda.getImplMethodSignature() by parsing the JVM field types of the method signature. The result is a MethodType which contains the return type and the parameter types of the given lambda.

        Parameters:
        lambda - A serializable lambda.
        Returns:
        The signature of the lambda as MethodType.
